description: The blast of the WW2 bomb in a canal in Poland was not unexpected and divers were unharmed.
title: WW2 'earthquake' bomb explodes in Poland during attempt to defuse it
title_page: WW2 'earthquake' bomb explodes in Poland during attempt to defuse it - BBC News
maintext: "The deflagration process turned into detonation. The object can be considered neutralised, it will not pose any more threat to the Szczecin-Swinoujscie shipping channel," said Lt Cmdr Grzegorz Lewandowski, spokesman for the Polish Navy's 8th Coastal Defence Flotilla.
